Package interpreter

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Command
    Class to create command objects with command type and arguments.
    CommandAdd
    Class for Add command, which contains task name, 2 sets of date and time, a list of tags , a location and boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandDelete
    Class for Delete command, which contains line codes to identify task to delete, and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandDeleteLocation
    Class for Delete Location command, which contains a search string and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandDeleteName
    Class for Delete Name command, which contains a search string and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandDeleteTag
    Class for Search Tag command, which contains a String tag and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandDeleteTime
    Class for Delete Time command, which contains 2 sets of date and time and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandDone
    Class for Done command, which contains a string to indicate the task to be checked/unchecked as don and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandHelp
    Class for Help command, which contains a string to indicate type of view and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandSearchLocation
    Class for Search Location command, which contains a search string and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandSearchName
    Class for Search Name command, which contains a search string and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandSearchTag
    Class for Search Tag command, which contains a String tag and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandSearchTime
    Class for Search Time command, which contains 2 sets of date and time and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandUpdate
    Class for Update command, which contains line code to identify task to update, and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    CommandView
    Class for View command, which contains a string to indicate type of view and a boolean variable to indicate missing arguments.
    Interpreter
    Parses the command and returns a command object identifying the correct command and arguments.
